      "name": "Monoclonal B-cell lymphocytosis chronic lymphocytic leukemia-type",
      "definitions": [
        {
          "rootSource": "NCI",
          "sourceIdentifier": null,
          "value": "Monoclonal B-cell lymphocytosis characterized by the presence of more than 5 x 10^9/L abnormal B-lymphocytes in peripheral blood and presence of the characteristic immunophenotype of chronic lymphocytic leukemia. This type of monoclonal B-cell lymphocytosis evolves to chronic lymphocytic leukemia at a rate of 1-2% per year.",
